<paragraph blockId="6.[151,927,870,897]" box="[151,927,870,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,927,870,897]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,927,870,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
Key to males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1902" box="[352,541,870,897]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,541,870,897]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">Sandalodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(based on gonopod structures)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="266" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,933,955]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,933,955]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">1 Acropodite process with a prominent, subtriangular secondary process on the lateral side............................ 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,962,984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,962,984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">- Acropodite process without a secondary process............................................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,992,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,992,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
2 (1) Acropodite process rounded, curved mesad (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schubart, O." box="[692,833,992,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="165 - 202" refId="ref6122" refString="Schubart, O. (1946) Contribuicao ao conhecimento do genero Leptodesmus (Familia Leptodesmidae, Diplopoda). Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 18, 165 - 202." type="journal article" year="1946">Schubart 1946</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 4)..................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schubart, 1946)" baseAuthorityName="Schubart" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[1174,1436,992,1014]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araujoi">
<emphasis box="[1174,1269,992,1013]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">S. araujoi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schubart, O." box="[1281,1429,992,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="165 - 202" refId="ref6122" refString="Schubart, O. (1946) Contribuicao ao conhecimento do genero Leptodesmus (Familia Leptodesmidae, Diplopoda). Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 18, 165 - 202." type="journal article" year="1946">Schubart, 1946</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
- Acropodite process subtriangular, projected up (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Silvestri, F." box="[725,861,1021,1043]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref6358" refString="Silvestri, F. (1895) Viaggio del dottor Alfredo Borelli nella Repubblica Argentina e nel Paraguay. XIV. Chilopodi e Diplopodi. Bollettino del musei di zoologia e di anatomia comparata della Reale Universita di Torino, 10 (203), 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 8048" type="journal article" year="1895">Silvestri 1895</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[935,1077,1021,1043]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="247 - 259" refId="ref5695" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1982) Chelodesmid studies. XVIII. A synopsis of the genus Sandalodesmus Silvestri, 1902, and proposal of the new tribe Sandalodesmini (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Spixiana, 5 (3), 247 - 259. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 28194567" type="journal article" year="1982">Hoffman 1982</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1, 2)................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Silvestri, 1895)" baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1153,1436,1050,1072]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salvadorii">
<emphasis box="[1153,1274,1050,1072]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">S. salvadorii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silvestri, F." box="[1287,1429,1050,1072]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref6358" refString="Silvestri, F. (1895) Viaggio del dottor Alfredo Borelli nella Repubblica Argentina e nel Paraguay. XIV. Chilopodi e Diplopodi. Bollettino del musei di zoologia e di anatomia comparata della Reale Universita di Torino, 10 (203), 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 8048" type="journal article" year="1895">Silvestri, 1895</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,1080,1102]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1080,1102]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">3 (1) Prefemur short, less than half of the total length of telopodite, not extending distad beyond base of the prefemoral process.. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="266">- Prefemur longer, more than half of the total length of telopodite, extending distad to about midlength of prefemoral process.. ................................................................................................... 9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
4 (3) Acropodite short, scarcely longer than prefemoral process, its distal edge exceeded by solenomere (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schubart, O." box="[1206,1358,1167,1190]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="77 - 132" refId="ref6155" refString="Schubart, O. (1954 a) Sobre os Diplopoda dos estados do Parana e Santa Catarina. I. Proterospermophora. Arquivos do Museu Paranaense, 10, 77 - 132." type="journal article" year="1954">Schubart 1954a</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 16) …......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schubart, 1954)" baseAuthorityName="Schubart" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[1141,1436,1197,1219]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camellatus">
<emphasis box="[1141,1269,1197,1218]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">S. camellatus</emphasis>
(Schubart, 1954)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,1226,1248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1226,1248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">- Acropodite long, forming a concave shield that contains the solenomere......................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,1255,1278]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1255,1278]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">5 (4) Prefemoral process shorter than acropodite................................................................. 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
- Prefemoral process as long as acropodite, apically broad and rounded in mesal aspect, without a basal lobe; acropodite with a prominent spiculate lobe on the lateral side (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schubart, O." box="[690,831,1314,1336]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="23 - 32" refId="ref6273" refString="Schubart, O. (1958) &quot; Leptodesmidae &quot; Brasileiras. VI: Especies novas do Estado do Rio Grande do Sul (Diplopoda, Proterosper- mophora). Revista brasileira de biologia, 18 (1), 23 - 32." type="journal article" year="1958">Schubart 1958</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 4).................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schubart, 1958)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Schubart" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[1156,1436,1314,1336]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="repandus">
<emphasis box="[1156,1268,1314,1336]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">S. repandus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schubart, O." box="[1281,1429,1314,1336]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="23 - 32" refId="ref6273" refString="Schubart, O. (1958) &quot; Leptodesmidae &quot; Brasileiras. VI: Especies novas do Estado do Rio Grande do Sul (Diplopoda, Proterosper- mophora). Revista brasileira de biologia, 18 (1), 23 - 32." type="journal article" year="1958">Schubart, 1958</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,1343,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1343,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">6 (5) Nontorsate prefemoral process.......................................................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,1373,1395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1373,1395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">- Torsate prefemoral process............................................................................. 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,1402,1424]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1402,1424]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
7 (6) Solenomere massive and apically reflexed (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[682,824,1402,1424]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="247 - 259" refId="ref5695" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1982) Chelodesmid studies. XVIII. A synopsis of the genus Sandalodesmus Silvestri, 1902, and proposal of the new tribe Sandalodesmini (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Spixiana, 5 (3), 247 - 259. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 28194567" type="journal article" year="1982">Hoffman 1982</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 5)...................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 1982" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="1982" box="[1175,1436,1402,1424]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avilectus">
<emphasis box="[1175,1284,1402,1424]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">S. avilectus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[1290,1436,1402,1424]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="247 - 259" refId="ref5695" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1982) Chelodesmid studies. XVIII. A synopsis of the genus Sandalodesmus Silvestri, 1902, and proposal of the new tribe Sandalodesmini (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Spixiana, 5 (3), 247 - 259. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 28194567" type="journal article" year="1982">Hoffman, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1436,1431,1454]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1431,1454]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
- Solenomere not massive (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schubart, O." box="[511,664,1431,1454]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="113 - 146" refId="ref6189" refString="Schubart, O. (1954 b) Diplopodos Argentinos del Museo de la Ciudad Eva Peron. I. Familia Leptodesmidae. Ministerio de educacion de la nacion. Universidad nacional de Eva Peron. Notas del Museo, 17, 113 - 146." type="journal article" year="1954">Schubart 1954b</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 14)............................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schubart, 1954)" baseAuthorityName="Schubart" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[1133,1436,1431,1454]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iguazuensis">
<emphasis box="[1133,1269,1432,1453]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">S. iguazuensis</emphasis>
(Schubart, 1954)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
8 (6) Prefemoral process large, concave, excavated to accommodate the acropodite (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[1020,1162,1461,1483]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="247 - 259" refId="ref5695" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1982) Chelodesmid studies. XVIII. A synopsis of the genus Sandalodesmus Silvestri, 1902, and proposal of the new tribe Sandalodesmini (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Spixiana, 5 (3), 247 - 259. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 28194567" type="journal article" year="1982">Hoffman 1982</bibRefCitation>
, figs 3, 4)............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 1982" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="1982" box="[1181,1436,1490,1512]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Sandalodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="librellus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1284,1490,1512]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">S. librellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[1290,1436,1490,1512]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266" pagination="247 - 259" refId="ref5695" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1982) Chelodesmid studies. XVIII. A synopsis of the genus Sandalodesmus Silvestri, 1902, and proposal of the new tribe Sandalodesmini (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Spixiana, 5 (3), 247 - 259. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 28194567" type="journal article" year="1982">Hoffman, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,933,1894]" box="[151,1437,1520,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
<keyLead box="[151,1437,1520,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">
- Prefemoral process small, Z-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[582,662,1520,1542]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sexual characters of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. A. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, mesal view. B. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, lateral view. C. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, ventral view. D. Paratype ♀ (FCE-Myr 0664), left vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Ev: external valve; Iv: internal valve; Op: operculum; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A–C), 0.2 mm (D). Photographed by: Damián Hagopián." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621311/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[672,703,1520,1542]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,697,721]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,187,670]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,673]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopod drawings of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp., holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod. A. Mesal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621313/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="266">4A</figureCitation>
).............................. 
